# Databricks notebook source
# discharge_planning_phase1_v1_6.py
# Version: v1.6
# Author: isultan@khcc.jo
# Description: Phase 1 structured extraction for the Discharge Planning
#   before/after intervention study at KHCC. Pulls ~35 structured variables
#   per inpatient encounter discharged July–December 2025 from silver/gold
#   tables and writes results to dbo.silver_discharge_planning_structured.
#   LLM variables (functional status, comorbidities, etc.) are Phase 2.
#
# Changes from v1.5:
#   [FIX H] is_surgical_case over-firing (was 56%, expected ~15-20%):
#           LIKE '%SURG%' on WARD_LOCATION matched medical wards named
#           'KHCC-3B-MEDICAL/SURGICAL', 'KHCC-4B-MEDICAL/SURGICAL' etc.
#           Fix: surgical detection now uses an explicit IN list of confirmed
#           surgical FACILITY_TREATING_SPECIALTY values (from Query 1 results),
#           plus SURGICAL ONCOLOGY wildcard, plus exact ward KHCC-3C-SURGERY.
#           WARD_LOCATION LIKE '%SURG%' removed.
#   [FIX I] 7d/30d readmission + ED revisit all 0%:
#           silver_readmissions and silver_er_revisits are stale — 0 rows
#           for Jul-Dec 2025 (pipeline not running on schedule).
#           Fix: readmissions now computed directly from silver_admissions
#           self-join (same MRN, new HOSPITALIZATION_DATE within 7/30 days
#           of DISCHARGE_DATE). ED revisit from silver_er_admission_discharge
#           if available, otherwise from vista_notes ER document types.

